<HEADLINE> Kenya To Host African Women Educators Forum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 22 (Xinhua) -- The General Assembly of African
Women Educators Forum (AEF) will open in Nanyuki, 200 kilometers
north of Nairobi, capital of Kenya on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
AEF's 43 members from 26 countries and African education
ministers are expected to attend the five-day meeting at Kenya's
equatorial town.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will be preceded by a media workshop involving
about 20 journalists and editors who will discuss the role of the
media in the effort to educate girls and women in development.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, the AEF organizer said the AEF is to enhance
political commitment towards the goal of "education for all" and
urge government donors and non-governmental organizations to
invest more in the education sector especially in the education
of girls. 
</P>
